<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900608-0066</DOCNO><DOCID>900608-0066.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Playboy Enterprises Inc.:   Recapitalization Completed   After Approval of Measure</HL><DATE>06/08/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7</SO><CO>   PLAA H.IEP A.BRY</CO><IN>DIVIDENDS (DIV)</IN><LP>   Playboy Enterprises Inc., Chicago, said it completed arecapitalization plan, under which it will convert its commonstock into voting and nonvoting classes.   The proposal was criticized by some holders, but passagewas never in question, as it had the support of Hugh M.Hefner, founder and former chairman, who holds a 71% stake inthe publishing and entertainment concern.</LP><TEXT>   After the measure was approved, Playboy said, it carriedout a 1-for-2 reverse split of its common stock, andreclassified that reduced number of shares as voting Class Astock. It then paid a stock dividend of three shares of newnonvoting Class B common stock for each share of Class Acommon. The two classes will trade separately on the New YorkStock Exchange, beginning today, Playboy said.   The dual-class arrangement will allow Mr. Hefner, shouldhe wish to do so, to retain his majority voting stake whileshedding up to three-quarters of his shares. That was whatirked some shareholders, including Industrial Equity(Pacific) Ltd., which has a 7.6% Playboy stake.</TEXT></DOC>